objects.name: cheeky chipmunk
objects.description: Cheeky Chipmunk is a malicious Microsoft Windows Remote Procedure Call (RPC) server which is installed via a PowerShell loader and tasked by a separate RPC client.

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: Turla is a threat actor that has been previously observed using single-byte XOR-encoding of imported function names with 0x55.

objects.name: CVE-2021-44228
objects.description: No specific vulnerability is mentioned in the report, however, the report does discuss the exploitation of vulnerabilities in general.

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_command_argument_check
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CheekyChipmunk_command_argument_check { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects Cheeky Chipmunk argument checking code to determine command to process. " date = "2022-01-24" hash1 = "7e4a6bac09ad214e98801bc199f96c265d7b6b48" strings: $1 = {66 83 F8 70 75 ?? C7 85 ?? FD FF FF 01 00 00 00 EB ??} $2 = {66 83 F8 63 75 ?? C7 85 ?? FD FF FF 03 00 00 00 EB ??} $3 = {66 83 F8 67 75 ?? C7 85 ?? FD FF FF 02 00 00 00 EB ??} $4 = {66 83 F8 72 75 ?? C7 85 ?? FD FF FF 01 00 00 00 EB ??} condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: CheekyChipmunk_GUID_bytes
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern: rule CheekyChipmunk_GUID_bytes { meta: author = "NCSC" description = "Detects the Cheeky Chipmunk RPC GUID" date = "2022-01-24" hash1 = "52c8cbd0545caab7596c1382c7fc5a479209851d" hash2 = "865f4c457bf86ff03456de828044f6ed6d6cf96a" hash3 = "5d5825b14377c5e5fe96816dd72a90bd13dc9fc8" hash4 = "7e4a6bac09ad214e98801bc199f96c265d7b6b48" strings: $GUID = {64 25 F0 7D 1E C3 68 4A A6 88 72 D0 EC 84 07 46} condition: uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and all of them }

objects.name: T1543.003
objects.description: Create or Modify System Process: Windows Service. Cheeky Chipmunk maintains persistence by adding a new Windows service (pnrssp) for the RPC server component.

objects.name: T1059.001
objects.description: Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell. Open-source PowerShell runner code is embedded in the Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server and used to invoke commands stored in the registry.

objects.name: T1059.003
objects.description: Command and Scripting Interpreter: Windows Command Shell. The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server can be sent Windows shell commands by the RPC client.

objects.name: T1559.001
objects.description: Inter-Process Communication: Component Object Model. The Cheeky Chipmunk RPC server uses COM to call embedded PowerShell runner code.

objects.name: T1047
objects.description: No specific description is provided for this technique in the report.

objects.name: T1140
objects.description: No specific description is provided for this technique in the report.

objects.name: T1070.004
objects.description: Indicator Removal on Host: File Deletion. The Cheeky Chipmunk loader uses built-in and open-source PowerShell libraries to Base64-decode, 3DES-decrypt, and GZIP-decompress the RPC server. The Cheeky Chipmunk loader is deleted from disk once the RPC server is running.

objects.name: T1036.005
objects.description: Masquerading: Match Legitimate Name or Location. Cheeky Chipmunk masquerades as a legitimate Windows service path (netsvcs) to maintain persistence.

objects.name: T1027
objects.description: Obfuscated Files or Information. Cheeky Chipmunk’s import names are obfuscated by XORing with 0x55.

objects.name: T1562.001
objects.description: Impair Defenses: Disable or Modify Tools. Cheeky Chipmunk implements an AMSI bypass technique.

objects.name: T1005
objects.description: Data from Local System. Cheeky Chipmunk can be tasked to collect files.
